#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:60
msgid "Landing page architecture"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:62
msgid ""
"The frontend uses a three-route flow: landing page → auth callback → "
"dashboard. The authentication callback behaves differently depending on "
"whether the user selected a citizen IdP or the caseworker option."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:64
msgid "**1. Landing Page (`/` — `LoginChoice.tsx`)**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:66
msgid ""
"Identity provider selection page with four buttons. Three are for citizens "
"(orange DigiD, blue eHerkenning, indigo eIDAS); one is for caseworkers "
"(slate \"Inloggen als Medewerker\"), visually separated by a \"MEDEWERKERS\" "
"section divider."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:68
msgid ""
"const handleIDPSelection = (\n"
"  idp: \"digid\" | \"eherkenning\" | \"eidas\" | \"medewerker\",\n"
") => {\n"
"  sessionStorage.setItem(\"selected_idp\", idp);\n"
"  navigate(\"/auth\");\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:77
msgid ""
"The selected value is stored in `sessionStorage` under the key "
"`selected_idp` and read by `AuthCallback.tsx`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:79
msgid "**2. Authentication Callback (`/auth` — `AuthCallback.tsx`)**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:81
msgid ""
"The callback reads `selected_idp` and branches on whether the user is a "
"caseworker."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:83
msgid "**Citizen path (digid / eherkenning / eidas):**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:85
msgid ""
"const initOptions = {\n"
"  onLoad: \"login-required\",\n"
"  checkLoginIframe: false,\n"
"  idpHint: selectedIdp, // 'digid' | 'eherkenning' | 'eidas'\n"
"};\n"
"const authenticated = await keycloak.init(initOptions);"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:94
msgid ""
"`onLoad: 'login-required'` triggers an immediate OIDC redirect. The "
"`idpHint` tells Keycloak to skip its native login form and redirect straight "
"to the chosen external identity provider (DigiD, eHerkenning, or eIDAS). In "
"the test environment where real IdPs are not configured, Keycloak falls back "
"to its native form without a context banner."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:96
msgid "**Caseworker path (medewerker):**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:98
msgid ""
"// Step 1: silent SSO check — no redirect triggered\n"
"const authenticated = await keycloak.init({\n"
"  onLoad: \"check-sso\",\n"
"  checkLoginIframe: false,\n"
"});\n"
"\n"
"if (authenticated) {\n"
"  // Existing SSO session found — go straight to dashboard\n"
"  navigate(\"/dashboard\", { replace: true });\n"
"} else {\n"
"  // No session — redirect to Keycloak with sentinel\n"
"  await keycloak.login({ loginHint: \"__medewerker__\" });\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:114
msgid ""
"`onLoad: 'check-sso'` returns `true` if a Keycloak SSO session cookie "
"already exists in the browser, allowing the caseworker to skip the login "
"screen entirely on subsequent visits within the session window. If no "
"session exists, `keycloak.login({ loginHint: '__medewerker__' })` redirects "
"to Keycloak and passes `__medewerker__` as the `login_hint` parameter. The "
"`login.ftl` template detects this sentinel and renders the caseworker "
"context banner (see [Keycloak Deployment — Caseworker banner]{1})."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:116
msgid ""
"**3. Caseworker dashboard (`/dashboard/caseworker` — "
"`CaseworkerDashboard.tsx`)**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:118
msgid ""
"The caseworker portal. This route is **not wrapped in `ProtectedRoute`** — "
"authentication is handled inside the component so public content (Nieuws, "
"Berichten, Regelcatalogus) can render without a login. The component checks "
"`keycloak.authenticated` on mount:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:119
msgid "const [isAuthenticated] = useState(() => !!keycloak.authenticated);"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:123
msgid ""
"The shell renders three zones driven by `tenantConfig` loaded from `public/"
"tenants.json`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cfrontend-development.md:125
msgid ""
"**Top nav** — six `TopNavPage` values: `home | personal-info | projects | "
"audit-log | gereedschap | iou`. The `audit-log` and `gereedschap` tabs are "
"platform-scoped (hardcoded, not in `tenants.json`). The `iou` tab is tenant-"
